    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="490" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                <head>No. 491.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Peixotto</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-07-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 22,
                                        1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 34.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 33, of the 24th
                                ultimo, has been received. It is learned with regret that justice
                                has been denied to the Hebrews in Roumania. The Department has
                                complied with your suggestion, that an instruction be addressed to
                                certain ministers of the United States in Europe, directing them to
                                employ moral efforts toward inducing the governments to which they
                                are accredited to forward an adjustment of the question.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
